<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-01-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-01-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="18" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d18">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.22/1–2247: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Myers</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-01-22">January 22,
                                1947</date>.<lb/>[Received January 22—5:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>23. General court-martial in the case of United States vs William G.
                            Pierson found the accused guilty of rape (reference my 331, December
                            30). Sentence was not announced as it must await approval of convening
                            authority.</p>
                        <p>Sent Department as 23; repeated Nanking as 15.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Myers</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>